{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.x"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"competition","sourceId":140389,"databundleVersionId":17067703}],"dockerImageVersionId":31400,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"d052f80f-4486-49c1-847d-63ec8349ee2e","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Maze Crawler — Heuristic Agent Notebook\n\nThis notebook creates a single-file `main.py` agent for the Kaggle **Maze Crawler / Crawl** challenge. The strategy is deliberately dependency-free and submission-safe: build a small economy, use scouts for fog/crystals, use workers to cut north walls, and create a miner when a mining node is visible.\n\nThe final cell packages `main.py` into `submission.tar.gz`, which you can submit to Kaggle.","metadata":{}},{"id":"df1fec9b-e445-43bc-8ccd-1f06abdf4519","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Strategy summary\n\nThe rules reward survival first, then total energy / unit count at the time limit. This agent therefore prioritizes:\n\n1. **Factory survival:** keep moving north, jump over blocked north walls only when the landing cell is safe.\n2. **Early worker:** one worker removes walls so the factory does not stall.\n3. **Scouts:** cheap vision and crystal collection; scouts are especially useful because they move every turn.\n4. **Opportunistic mining:** if a mining node becomes visible, build a miner and transform on the node.\n5. **Friendly-fire avoidance:** reserve planned cells and avoid stepping onto friendly units where possible.\n\nThis is meant as a strong baseline you can iterate on, not a final leaderboard solution.","metadata":{}},{"id":"bce248f5-1e69-4d2b-a06f-28632c57983e","cell_type":"code","source":"%%writefile main.py\n# Maze Crawler heuristic agent\n# Submission file: main.py\n# No external dependencies; safe for Kaggle agent runtime.\n\nfrom collections import deque\n\nFACTORY, SCOUT, WORKER, MINER = 0, 1, 2, 3\nWALL = {\"NORTH\": 1, \"EAST\": 2, \"SOUTH\": 4, \"WEST\": 8}\nDELTA = {\"NORTH\": (0, 1), \"EAST\": (1, 0), \"SOUTH\": (0, -1), \"WEST\": (-1, 0)}\nDIRS = (\"NORTH\", \"EAST\", \"WEST\", \"SOUTH\")\n\n\ndef _cfg(config, name, default):\n    \"\"\"Read Kaggle config fields whether config is an object or dict.\"\"\"\n    return getattr(config, name, config.get(name, default) if isinstance(config, dict) else default)\n\n\ndef _parse_pos_key(key):\n    c, r = key.split(\",\")\n    return int(c), int(r)\n\n\ndef _cell_wall(obs, config, col, row):\n    width = _cfg(config, \"width\", 20)\n    idx = (row - obs.southBound) * width + col\n    if 0 <= idx < len(obs.walls):\n        w = obs.walls[idx]\n        if w != -1:\n            return w\n    # Unknown cells: optimistic, because unseen walls are not reliably known yet.\n    return 0\n\n\ndef _in_bounds(obs, config, col, row):\n    width = _cfg(config, \"width\", 20)\n    return 0 <= col < width and obs.southBound <= row <= obs.northBound\n\n\ndef _can_step(obs, config, col, row, direction):\n    dc, dr = DELTA[direction]\n    nc, nr = col + dc, row + dr\n    if not _in_bounds(obs, config, nc, nr):\n        return False\n    return not (_cell_wall(obs, config, col, row) & WALL[direction])\n\n\ndef _passable_dirs(obs, config, col, row, allow_south=False):\n    out = []\n    for d in DIRS:\n        if d == \"SOUTH\" and not allow_south:\n            # The scrolling boundary makes south moves expensive unless trapped.\n            continue\n        if _can_step(obs, config, col, row, d):\n            dc, dr = DELTA[d]\n            nc, nr = col + dc, row + dr\n            # Avoid stepping onto the exact southern edge unless desperate.\n            if d == \"SOUTH\" and nr <= obs.southBound:\n                continue\n            out.append(d)\n    return out\n\n\ndef _nearest_step(obs, config, start, targets, avoid=set(), max_depth=80):\n    \"\"\"Return first direction on a short BFS route to any target cell.\"\"\"\n    if not targets:\n        return None\n    width = _cfg(config, \"width\", 20)\n    sc, sr = start\n    q = deque([(sc, sr, None, 0)])\n    seen = {(sc, sr)}\n    target_set = set(targets)\n\n    while q:\n        c, r, first, dist = q.popleft()\n        if (c, r) in target_set and first is not None:\n            return first\n        if dist >= max_depth:\n            continue\n        for d in DIRS:\n            if not _can_step(obs, config, c, r, d):\n                continue\n            dc, dr = DELTA[d]\n            nc, nr = c + dc, r + dr\n            if not (0 <= nc < width and obs.southBound <= nr <= obs.northBound):\n                continue\n            if nr <= obs.southBound and d == \"SOUTH\":\n                continue\n            if (nc, nr) in avoid and (nc, nr) not in target_set:\n                continue\n            if (nc, nr) in seen:\n                continue\n            seen.add((nc, nr))\n            q.append((nc, nr, d if first is None else first, dist + 1))\n    return None\n\n\ndef _best_target_from_values(pos, items, row_bias=3.0, value_bias=1.0):\n    \"\"\"Pick a visible target using distance, energy value, and northward progress.\"\"\"\n    if not items:\n        return None\n    c0, r0 = pos\n    def score(item):\n        c, r, value = item\n        dist = abs(c - c0) + abs(r - r0)\n        return dist * 8 - value * value_bias - max(0, r - r0) * row_bias\n    c, r, _ = min(items, key=score)\n    return (c, r)\n\n\ndef _frontier_targets(obs, config, limit=40):\n    \"\"\"Cells next to unknown cells; useful when no crystal/node is visible.\"\"\"\n    width = _cfg(config, \"width\", 20)\n    targets = []\n    for r in range(obs.southBound, obs.northBound + 1):\n        for c in range(width):\n            idx = (r - obs.southBound) * width + c\n            if not (0 <= idx < len(obs.walls)) or obs.walls[idx] == -1:\n                continue\n            unknown_neighbors = 0\n            for dc, dr in DELTA.values():\n                nc, nr = c + dc, r + dr\n                if 0 <= nc < width and obs.southBound <= nr <= obs.northBound:\n                    nidx = (nr - obs.southBound) * width + nc\n                    if 0 <= nidx < len(obs.walls) and obs.walls[nidx] == -1:\n                        unknown_neighbors += 1\n            if unknown_neighbors:\n                # Prefer northern frontiers so the factory doesn't get swallowed.\n                targets.append((c, r, r * 2 + unknown_neighbors))\n    targets.sort(key=lambda x: x[2], reverse=True)\n    return [(c, r) for c, r, _ in targets[:limit]]\n\n\ndef _safe_greedy_move(obs, config, col, row, avoid=set(), prefer=None, allow_south=False):\n    \"\"\"Fallback movement: push north, then sideways, then south only if trapped.\"\"\"\n    prefs = []\n    if prefer:\n        prefs.append(prefer)\n    prefs += [\"NORTH\", \"EAST\", \"WEST\"]\n    if allow_south:\n        prefs.append(\"SOUTH\")\n    for d in prefs:\n        if d not in DIRS:\n            continue\n        if _can_step(obs, config, col, row, d):\n            dc, dr = DELTA[d]\n            target = (col + dc, row + dr)\n            if target in avoid:\n                continue\n            if d == \"SOUTH\" and target[1] <= obs.southBound:\n                continue\n            return d\n    # Desperation: if completely boxed, any legal south move is better than no action.\n    if not allow_south:\n        return _safe_greedy_move(obs, config, col, row, avoid, prefer, allow_south=True)\n    return \"IDLE\"\n\n\ndef _direction_toward(src, dst):\n    if dst is None:\n        return None\n    c, r = src\n    tc, tr = dst\n    if tr > r:\n        return \"NORTH\"\n    if tc > c:\n        return \"EAST\"\n    if tc < c:\n        return \"WEST\"\n    if tr < r:\n        return \"SOUTH\"\n    return None\n\n\ndef _spawn_direction(obs, config, col, row, occupied):\n    \"\"\"Pick a free adjacent build cell. North is best, side-spawns avoid blocked fronts.\"\"\"\n    for d in (\"NORTH\", \"EAST\", \"WEST\", \"SOUTH\"):\n        if not _can_step(obs, config, col, row, d):\n            continue\n        dc, dr = DELTA[d]\n        pos = (col + dc, row + dr)\n        if pos in occupied:\n            continue\n        # Avoid spawning onto the southern edge unless no other option.\n        if d == \"SOUTH\" and pos[1] <= obs.southBound:\n            continue\n        return d\n    return None\n\n\ndef agent(obs, config):\n    actions = {}\n    if not getattr(obs, \"robots\", None):\n        return actions\n\n    scout_cost = _cfg(config, \"scoutCost\", 50)\n    worker_cost = _cfg(config, \"workerCost\", 200)\n    miner_cost = _cfg(config, \"minerCost\", 300)\n    wall_remove_cost = _cfg(config, \"wallRemoveCost\", 100)\n    transform_cost = _cfg(config, \"transformCost\", 100)\n\n    my = {}\n    enemies = {}\n    for uid, data in obs.robots.items():\n        if len(data) < 5:\n            continue\n        rtype, col, row, energy, owner = data[:5]\n        rec = {\n            \"type\": rtype, \"col\": col, \"row\": row, \"energy\": energy, \"owner\": owner,\n            \"move_cd\": data[5] if len(data) > 5 else 0,\n            \"jump_cd\": data[6] if len(data) > 6 else 0,\n            \"build_cd\": data[7] if len(data) > 7 else 0,\n        }\n        if owner == obs.player:\n            my[uid] = rec\n        else:\n            enemies[uid] = rec\n\n    occupied = {(r[\"col\"], r[\"row\"]) for r in my.values()}\n    enemy_pos = {(r[\"col\"], r[\"row\"]): r for r in enemies.values()}\n    reserved = set()\n\n    counts = {FACTORY: 0, SCOUT: 0, WORKER: 0, MINER: 0}\n    for r in my.values():\n        counts[r[\"type\"]] = counts.get(r[\"type\"], 0) + 1\n\n    crystals = []\n    for key, val in getattr(obs, \"crystals\", {}).items():\n        c, r = _parse_pos_key(key)\n        crystals.append((c, r, int(val)))\n\n    nodes = []\n    for key in getattr(obs, \"miningNodes\", {}).keys():\n        c, r = _parse_pos_key(key)\n        nodes.append((c, r, 80))\n\n    friendly_mines = []\n    for key, m in getattr(obs, \"mines\", {}).items():\n        if len(m) >= 3 and m[2] == obs.player:\n            c, r = _parse_pos_key(key)\n            friendly_mines.append((c, r, int(m[0]) if m else 0))\n\n    frontiers = _frontier_targets(obs, config)\n\n    # Handle factories first: they control production and survival.\n    ordered = sorted(my.items(), key=lambda kv: (0 if kv[1][\"type\"] == FACTORY else 1, kv[1][\"row\"]))\n\n    for uid, r in ordered:\n        rtype, col, row, energy = r[\"type\"], r[\"col\"], r[\"row\"], r[\"energy\"]\n        pos = (col, row)\n        avoid = (occupied | reserved) - {pos}\n\n        # If a visible enemy is adjacent and weaker, opportunistically crush it.\n        attack_dir = None\n        for d in DIRS:\n            if not _can_step(obs, config, col, row, d):\n                continue\n            dc, dr = DELTA[d]\n            ep = (col + dc, row + dr)\n            er = enemy_pos.get(ep)\n            if er is not None and rtype > er[\"type\"]:\n                attack_dir = d\n                break\n\n        if rtype == FACTORY:\n            # Build policy: one worker to cut walls, scouts for vision/crystals, then miners if nodes appear.\n            spawn_d = _spawn_direction(obs, config, col, row, occupied | reserved)\n            if spawn_d and r[\"build_cd\"] == 0:\n                # Visible nearby mining nodes justify a miner; otherwise scouts are very efficient.\n                if nodes and counts[MINER] < 1 and energy >= miner_cost + 250:\n                    actions[uid] = f\"BUILD_MINER_{spawn_d}\"\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[spawn_d][0], row + DELTA[spawn_d][1]))\n                    continue\n                if counts[WORKER] < 1 and energy >= worker_cost + 150:\n                    actions[uid] = f\"BUILD_WORKER_{spawn_d}\"\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[spawn_d][0], row + DELTA[spawn_d][1]))\n                    continue\n                if counts[SCOUT] < 3 and energy >= scout_cost + 150:\n                    actions[uid] = f\"BUILD_SCOUT_{spawn_d}\"\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[spawn_d][0], row + DELTA[spawn_d][1]))\n                    continue\n                if counts[WORKER] < 2 and energy >= worker_cost + 450:\n                    actions[uid] = f\"BUILD_WORKER_{spawn_d}\"\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[spawn_d][0], row + DELTA[spawn_d][1]))\n                    continue\n                if counts[SCOUT] < 6 and energy >= scout_cost + 500:\n                    actions[uid] = f\"BUILD_SCOUT_{spawn_d}\"\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[spawn_d][0], row + DELTA[spawn_d][1]))\n                    continue\n\n            if attack_dir and r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n                actions[uid] = attack_dir\n                reserved.add((col + DELTA[attack_dir][0], row + DELTA[attack_dir][1]))\n                continue\n\n            # Jump over a north wall only when the landing is safely inside the window.\n            if (_cell_wall(obs, config, col, row) & WALL[\"NORTH\"] and\n                r[\"move_cd\"] == 0 and r[\"jump_cd\"] == 0 and\n                row + 2 <= obs.northBound and (col, row + 2) not in avoid):\n                actions[uid] = \"JUMP_NORTH\"\n                reserved.add((col, row + 2))\n                continue\n\n            if r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n                target = _best_target_from_values(pos, crystals, row_bias=2.0, value_bias=0.7)\n                step = _nearest_step(obs, config, pos, [target] if target else frontiers, avoid=avoid)\n                move = step or _safe_greedy_move(obs, config, col, row, avoid)\n                actions[uid] = move\n                if move in DELTA:\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[move][0], row + DELTA[move][1]))\n            else:\n                actions[uid] = \"IDLE\"\n            continue\n\n        if rtype == MINER:\n            node_here = f\"{col},{row}\" in getattr(obs, \"miningNodes\", {})\n            if node_here and energy >= transform_cost + 15:\n                actions[uid] = \"TRANSFORM\"\n                continue\n            if attack_dir and r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n                actions[uid] = attack_dir\n                reserved.add((col + DELTA[attack_dir][0], row + DELTA[attack_dir][1]))\n                continue\n            if r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n                target = _best_target_from_values(pos, nodes, row_bias=1.5, value_bias=1.0)\n                step = _nearest_step(obs, config, pos, [target] if target else frontiers, avoid=avoid)\n                move = step or _safe_greedy_move(obs, config, col, row, avoid)\n                actions[uid] = move\n                if move in DELTA:\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[move][0], row + DELTA[move][1]))\n            else:\n                actions[uid] = \"IDLE\"\n            continue\n\n        if rtype == WORKER:\n            # Workers are wall cutters. If a wall blocks the useful direction, remove it.\n            target = _best_target_from_values(pos, crystals + nodes, row_bias=2.5, value_bias=0.7)\n            rough = _direction_toward(pos, target) or \"NORTH\"\n            if (_cell_wall(obs, config, col, row) & WALL.get(rough, 0)) and energy >= wall_remove_cost + 5:\n                actions[uid] = f\"REMOVE_{rough}\"\n                continue\n            if (_cell_wall(obs, config, col, row) & WALL[\"NORTH\"]) and energy >= wall_remove_cost + 5:\n                actions[uid] = \"REMOVE_NORTH\"\n                continue\n            if attack_dir and r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n                actions[uid] = attack_dir\n                reserved.add((col + DELTA[attack_dir][0], row + DELTA[attack_dir][1]))\n                continue\n            if r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n                step = _nearest_step(obs, config, pos, [target] if target else frontiers, avoid=avoid)\n                move = step or _safe_greedy_move(obs, config, col, row, avoid, prefer=rough)\n                actions[uid] = move\n                if move in DELTA:\n                    reserved.add((col + DELTA[move][0], row + DELTA[move][1]))\n            else:\n                actions[uid] = \"IDLE\"\n            continue\n\n        # Scouts: harvest visible crystals, open fog, and stay ahead of the scroll.\n        if attack_dir and r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n            actions[uid] = attack_dir\n            reserved.add((col + DELTA[attack_dir][0], row + DELTA[attack_dir][1]))\n            continue\n        if r[\"move_cd\"] == 0:\n            target = _best_target_from_values(pos, crystals, row_bias=3.5, value_bias=1.0)\n            step = _nearest_step(obs, config, pos, [target] if target else frontiers, avoid=avoid)\n            move = step or _safe_greedy_move(obs, config, col, row, avoid)\n            actions[uid] = move\n            if move in DELTA:\n                reserved.add((col + DELTA[move][0], row + DELTA[move][1]))\n        else:\n            actions[uid] = \"IDLE\"\n\n    return actions\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.152892Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.153216Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.170454Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.153185Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.169451Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Writing main.py\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":1},{"id":"57c9c887-2cbb-47be-a875-c231b95cb4ca","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Quick syntax check\n\nThis checks that `main.py` imports and exposes `agent`. It does not require the Kaggle environment package.","metadata":{}},{"id":"615017a0-c932-441a-bfe3-64f7832b7e83","cell_type":"code","source":"import importlib.util\nspec = importlib.util.spec_from_file_location('submission_main', 'main.py')\nmod = importlib.util.module_from_spec(spec)\nspec.loader.exec_module(mod)\nassert callable(mod.agent)\nprint('OK: main.py defines a callable agent(obs, config).')\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.172432Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.172871Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.200423Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.172830Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.199617Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"OK: main.py defines a callable agent(obs, config).\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":2},{"id":"4d9470bf-ec38-4361-b6ea-d3ed67825b4c","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Optional local smoke test\n\nRun this in Kaggle or locally after installing `kaggle-environments`. If the environment name is available, it plays a few seeds against the built-in random agent.","metadata":{}},{"id":"551fb031-2c26-4503-88c4-bfb38ad61873","cell_type":"code","source":"# Uncomment if needed:\n# !pip install -q kaggle-environments\n\ntry:\n    from kaggle_environments import make\n    for seed in [1, 2, 3, 42, 123]:\n        env = make('crawl', configuration={'randomSeed': seed}, debug=True)\n        env.run(['main.py', 'random'])\n        final = env.steps[-1]\n        print(seed, [(i, s.reward, s.status) for i, s in enumerate(final)])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('Smoke test skipped or failed in this runtime:')\n    print(repr(e))\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.201650Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.201983Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-29T10:55:17.184446Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-29T10:54:57.201951Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-29T10:55:17.183488Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"[kaggle_environments.envs.open_spiel_env.open_spiel_env] INFO: Successfully loaded OpenSpiel environments: 24.\n[kaggle_environments.envs.open_spiel_env.open_spiel_env] INFO:    open_spiel_amazons\n[kaggle_environments.envs.open_spiel_env.open_spiel_